{{Infobox company | name = IUCN World Commission on Protected Areas | logo = WCPA logo.svg | type = [[Committee|Commission]] | location = [[Gland, Switzerland]] | area_served = worldwide | key_people = Kathy MacKinnon (chair) | industry = [[conservation ethic|Nature conservation]] | products = IUCN Protected Areas Programme | services = [[Protected area]] planning, policy advice, and investment | equity = 2,400 members, 140 countries | parent = [[IUCN]] | divisions = America, Africa, Asia, and Europe | homepage = {{URL|cms.iucn.org/about/union/commissions/wcpa/index.cfm|IUCN website}} }}
The '''World Commission on Protected Areas''' ('''WCPA''') is one of six commissions of the [[International Union for Conservation of Nature]] (IUCN).<ref name="IUCN">{{cite web|url=http://cms.iucn.org/about/union/commissions/wcpa/index.cfm|title=World Commission on Protected Areas|publisher=[[IUCN]]|access-date=2008-09-07}}</ref> WCPA is the world's premier network of [[protected area]] expertise. It is administered by IUCN's Global Protected Areas Programme and has over 2,400 members, spanning 140 countries.
